  <note line="100" original="thīnaṃ (pī.)" reference-line="69" id="15">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">thinaṃ</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="pī." source="pali text society">thīnaṃ</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <snippet> katamaṃ byāpādanīvaraṇaṃ? Yo sattesu saṅkhāresu ca āghāto…pe… yathā dose tathā nioṭṭhānā, ayaṃ byāpādo nīvaraṇaṃ. Tattha katamaṃ middhaṃ? Yā cittassa jaḷatā cittassa garuttaṃ cittassa akammanīyatā cittassa nikkhepo niddāyanā pacalikatā pacalāyanā pacalāyanaṃ, idaṃ middhaṃ. Tattha katamaṃ thinaṃ </snippet>
  </note>
  <note line="109" original="kiṃ kaṃ (pī. ka.)" reference-line="70" id="16">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">Kathaṃ</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="pī." source="pali text society">kiṃ kaṃ</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="ka." source="cambodian">kiṃ kaṃ</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <snippet>Tattha nīvaraṇānīti ko vacanattho, kuto nivārayantīti? Sabbato kusalapakkhikā nivārayanti. Kathaṃ </snippet>
  </note>
  <note line="119" original="mettato (pī.)" reference-line="70" id="17">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">mettāya</alternative>
